 Modeling dynamic architectures<body>       Modeling Dynamic Architectures                      Darwin</strong>  Runtime reconfiguration of distributed systems.    DynamicACME</strong>  A set of extensions to the ACME ADL interchange language formodeling dynamism.    DynamicWright</strong>   </strong>A common notation for describing the static and dynamicaspects of an architecture.    Rapide</strong>  The set of components to which events are broadcast changes atruntime (using the link construct).   Return to the  Dynamic SoftwareArchitectures home page . These pages are maintained by  Peyman Oreizy .Send comments via  e-mail . </body> ï¿½  